  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Visual Merchandising",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary:</strong><br>\nWe are looking for a creative and passionate Visual Merchandiser to craft captivating in-store displays and layouts that showcase our client’s beauty products. The ideal candidate will have a keen eye for aesthetics, a deep understanding of current beauty trends, and will work closely with the brands VM teams to execute multiple projects across APAC region</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Working closely with brands on execution aligned with brand identity and seasonal campaigns.</li>\n  <li>Key communicator with brand’s VM team on guidelines.</li>\n  <li>Maintain consistent branding and visual standards across all store locations and displays.</li>\n  <li>Manage visual merchandising budgets and ensure cost-effective implementation of displays.</li>\n  <li>Working closely with local partners to arrange permit and manpower, ensure strong execution and prepare completion report.</li>\n  <li>Daily communication and weekly WIP report with brands.</li>\n  <li>Assistant to VM Director in all projects.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<p>Possess a diploma / degree in Visual Merchandising</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Proven experience in visual merchandising, particularly within      the beauty or cosmetics industry.</li>\n  <li>Strong aesthetic sense with a good understanding of beauty      trends.</li>\n  <li>Excellent creative, organizational, and communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently, manage multiple projects, and      meet deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of technical skills, retail display tools, and layout      software.</li>\n  <li>Flexibility to work outside of regular hours, including      weekends.</li>\n</ul>",
